  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's a good product for Acne?",
  "response": "Choosing the right product for acne depends on the severity and type of acne you have. Here are some effective options that are widely recommended:\n\n### **1. Salicylic Acid**\n   - **What it does:** Exfoliates skin, unclogs pores, and reduces inflammation.\n   - **Best for:** Mild to moderate acne (blackheads, whiteheads, and pimples).\n   - **Products:** CeraVe SA Cleanser, Paula's Choice 2% BHA Liquid Exfoliant.\n\n### **2. Benzoyl Peroxide**\n   - **What it does:** Kills acne-causing bacteria, reduces inflammation, and helps with clogged pores.\n   - **Best for:** Inflammatory acne (papules, pustules).\n   - **Products:** Panadoxy Benzoyl Peroxide 4% Wash, La Roche-Posay Effaclar Duo Acne Treatment.\n\n### **3. Retinoids (Retinol, Adapalene, Tretinoin)**\n   - **What it does:** Increases cell turnover, unclogs pores, and reduces acne scars.\n   - **Best for:** Mild to severe acne, including cystic acne.\n   - **Products:** Diferin Gel (Adapalene 0.1%), The Ordinary Retinol 0.5% in Squalane.\n\n### **4. Niacinamide**\n   - **What it does:** Reduces inflammation, regulates oil production, and improves the skin barrier.\n   - **Best for:** All skin types, including sensitive skin.\n   - **Products:** The Ordinary Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1%, Good Molecules Niacinamide Serum.\n\n### **5. Azelaic Acid**\n   - **What it does:** Reduces redness, unclogs pores, and has antibacterial properties.\n   - **Best for:** Mild to moderate acne, especially with redness or rosacea.\n   - **Products:** The Ordinary Azelaic Acid Suspension 10%, Paula's Choice Azelaic Acid Booster.\n\n### **6. Sulfur**\n   - **What it does:** Dries out pimples and absorbs excess oil.\n   - **Best for:** Spot treatment for inflammatory acne.\n   - **Products:** Peter Thomas Roth Therapeutic Sulfur Mask, De La Cruz Sulfur Ointment.\n\n### **7. Tea Tree Oil**\n   - **What it does:** Natural antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties.\n   - **Best for:** Mild acne.\n   - **Products:** The Body Shop Tea Tree Oil, Thursday Plantation Tea Tree Oil.\n\n### **8. Glycolic Acid**\n   - **What it does:** Exfoliates the skin and helps with clogged pores.\n   - **Best for:** Mild acne and acne scars.\n   - **Products:** Pixi Glow Tonic, The Ordinary Glycolic Acid 7% Toning Solution.\n\n### **Tips for Using Acne Products:**\n   - Start with a lower concentration to avoid irritation.\n   - Introduce one product at a time to monitor your skin's reaction.\n   - Always wear sunscreen, as some acne treatments can make your skin more sensitive to the sun.\n   - If over-the-counter products don\u2019t work, consult a dermatologist for prescription treatments like oral antibiotics or stronger retinoids.\n\n### **Prevention and Care:**\n   - Cleanse your face twice a day with a gentle, non-comedogenic cleanser.\n   - Avoid picking or popping pimples to prevent scarring.\n   - Use oil-free, non-comedogenic moisturizers and makeup.\n\nIf your acne is severe or persistent, it\u2019s best to consult a dermatologist for personalized treatment.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
